headline: Sysco (SYY): Evaluating Valuation as Shares Rise on Strong Profit Growth Forecasts and Improving Fundamentals
summary: If you hold shares of Sysco (SYY), or are considering getting in, the past few months have likely caught your attention. The company recently entered into a new $3 billion credit agreement, which formalizes its borrowing capacity but does not signal any dramatic shift in strategy. The real story is playing out in the share price, with Sysco’s stock steadily gaining ground thanks to growing confidence in its earnings outlook, rather than splashy news or headline-making deals.
